    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>The Brewster Congregational Church in Detroit, Michigan, was gathered in 1894. In 1924, the
        Brewster Congregational Church merged with the Pilgrim Congregational Church, gathered in
        1915, to form the Brewster Pilgrim Congregational Church. In 1957, the Brewster Pilgrim
        Congregational Church partnered with the Mount Hope Congregational Church, gathered 1889, to
        form the Pilgrim Congregational Church of Greater Detroit. This combined entity sold the
        Brewster Pilgrim Congregational Church building in 1957 and purchased a new building in
        Livonia, Michigan, which became the home of the newly reformed Pilgrim Congregational
        Church.</p>
      <p>The exact relationship between Mount Hope Congregational Church and the Pilgrim
        Congregational Church after 1958 is unclear; the churches seem to have operated
        independently after this point. The Mount Hope Congregational Church moved to Livonia in
        1964 and continues to serve the community today. The Pilgrim Congregational Church joined
        the United Church of Christ and between 1967 and 1969, the church was renamed to Pilgrim
        United Church of Christ. In 1969, the church federated with the Livonia Christian Church
        (Disciples of Christ). The Pilgrim United Church of Christ dissolved in 1979; in 1980 the
        church building was sold to the Livonia Christian Church.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>This collection contains the records of the Pilgrim United Church of Christ, Livonia,
        Michigan, and its various predecessor churches. The majority of this collection is vital
        records, such as Baptismal records, Marriage records, and membership records. The collection
        also contains some administrative records, including meeting minutes, correspondence, and
        legal records.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
